# Balanciz Project Guide Changelog

## v4 → v5

### Added

* Historical Honesty > Cosmetic Neatness as a formal core principle
* Cache = Acceleration ONLY as a formal core principle
* explicit shared architecture layers: Core Engines, Business Modules, Infrastructure Modules, Connector Layers
* Shared Cache Infrastructure as formal infrastructure
* SmartPicker Acceleration as formal infrastructure
* Report Acceleration as formal infrastructure
* AI Assist Platform as formal infrastructure
* FX / multi-currency rules for Journal Entry
* explicit FX source semantics separation (row origin vs JE snapshot source)
* explicit JE save-time FX rules
* Phase 1 FX rounding policy
* immutable posted JE FX read-path requirement
* historical honesty rules for FX and legacy data
* AR/AP foreign-currency control-account routing rules
* system-reserved account/code governance
* currencies / multi-currency controls under Company Settings
* additional audit / observability expectations around FX and cache behavior
* explicit requirement that report acceleration and picker acceleration remain subordinate to backend truth

### Expanded

* Product definition now explicitly includes FX and cache behavior in the supreme authority scope
* System architecture now formalizes reusable engine/module/connector layers
* Multi-company rules now explicitly include currencies and exchange rates as company-scoped data
* Posting Engine flow now includes FX / Currency Resolution
* Chart of Accounts now includes system-owned account rules and reserved-code namespaces
* Invoice direction now includes future compatibility with foreign-currency AR routing
* UI/UX principles now explicitly call out transaction-currency vs base-currency clarity
* Implementation checklist now includes historical honesty and cache/provider/AI subordination to backend truth
* Testing requirements now include provider contract correctness, no-live-provider-at-save, and honest legacy read semantics

### Clarified

* backend authority covers FX conversion and accounting truth
* external provider data is never accounting truth
* manual FX override must not mutate shared rate tables
* customer/vendor default transaction currency controls routing for new AR/AP documents
* historical uncertainty must be shown honestly rather than cosmetically normalized
* list/detail/reversal read surfaces must not disagree about legacy FX truth

### Directional Impact

* Balanciz is now explicitly governed as an engine-centered accounting platform with formal FX architecture, not just a single-currency bookkeeping core with later add-ons
* Multi-currency JE and future AR/AP foreign-currency routing are now part of the official architecture direction
* Shared acceleration and AI infrastructure are now first-class architecture concepts instead of ad hoc feature decisions
